<body>
    <h1>Task 18 -Technical Document</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h2 local-id=3D"fd04a991e0a3" id=3D"Task18-TechnicalDocument-1.Intr=
oduction"><strong>1. Introduction</strong></h2>
<h2 local-id=3D"d7aa57961392" id=3D"Task18-TechnicalDocument-1.1Purpose"><s=
trong>1.1 Purpose</strong></h2>
<p local-id=3D"68b15e35770c">This document provides a comprehensive technic=
al reference for deploying four independent websites on AWS infrastructure =
using a hybrid hosting model. The implementation combines direct web server=
 hosting via Nginx for Site 1 and Site 2, and load-balanced distributed hos=
ting via an Application Load Balancer (ALB) for Site 3 and Site 4. SSL/TLS =
encryption is enforced across all sites using AWS Certificate Manager (ACM)=
, and DNS routing is configured through Route 53.</p>
<p local-id=3D"7a5216984d0c">This document is intended for the following au=
diences:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"3d5efe7ad55a">CTO =E2=80=93 Strategic overview of the hybrid=
 hosting architecture and its business value for ABC Technologies</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"0f7b79a072d4">Developers =E2=80=93 Reference for Nginx virtu=
al host configuration, Flask application deployment, and per-site content m=
odification</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"436a55ac91e1">Solution Architects =E2=80=93 Design guidance =
for combining direct EC2 hosting with ALB-based distributed hosting</p></li=
>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"50976b47e73f">DevOps Engineers =E2=80=93 Step-by-step operat=
ional runbook for EC2 provisioning, Nginx setup, ALB configuration, SSL, an=
d DNS</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"d6270c5dee0c">Resellers / Partners =E2=80=93 Reference for c=
lient-facing multi-site hosting solution deliverables</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"93bc0e0fe66a" id=3D"Task18-TechnicalDocument-1.2Scope"><str=
ong>1.2 Scope</strong></h2>
<p local-id=3D"cfb228cab29f">This document covers the complete implementati=
on of the multi-site hosting task, including:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"d3028e7bfd1f">Provisioning of EC2 instances and installation=
 of Nginx for direct hosting of Site 1 and Site 2</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"336339b529aa">Configuration of Nginx server blocks (virtual =
hosts) to serve two independent websites from a single EC2 instance</p></li=
>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"f4a025a34202">Deployment of two additional EC2 instances hos=
ting the hello-world-flask GitHub project with modified per-site content fo=
r Site 3 and Site 4</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"b206b003c7de">Creation and configuration of an Application L=
oad Balancer with a target group, health checks, and HTTP listener</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"ab48f6a33f60">SSL/TLS certificate provisioning via ACM and C=
ertbot, with HTTP-to-HTTPS redirection enforced</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"28e9dbac9ee0">Route 53 DNS record creation mapping all four =
site subdomains to their respective infrastructure endpoints</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"bf2a2883cd41">End-to-end validation confirming correct conte=
nt, HTTPS access, and load balancing behavior</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h1 local-id=3D"d1b6d9fe8d2a" id=3D"Task18-TechnicalDocument-2.OverviewofDe=
vOpsProject"><strong>2. Overview of DevOps Project</strong></h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"2f433d8a97ca" id=3D"Task18-TechnicalDocument-2.1Definition"=
><strong>2.1 Definition</strong></h2>
<p local-id=3D"e65df2827364">This project implements a hybrid web hosting a=
rchitecture for ABC Technologies to demonstrate and evaluate two distinct a=
pproaches to hosting multiple web applications on AWS. The first approach u=
ses Nginx as a direct web server with virtual host configuration to serve m=
ultiple sites from a single EC2 instance =E2=80=94 optimal for lightweight,=
 static, or low-traffic applications. The second approach uses an Applicati=
on Load Balancer to distribute traffic across two EC2 instances =E2=80=94 o=
ptimal for scalable, high-availability applications requiring redundancy an=
d traffic distribution.</p>
<p local-id=3D"ce4950b5bff9">The base application for all four sites is the=
 hello-world-flask GitHub project (pushkar-iamops/hello-world-flask), a min=
imal Python Flask web application. Each site instance is modified to displa=
y a unique identifying message (Hello from Site 1 through Hello from Site 4=
), making load balancing behavior and routing observable through simple bro=
wser testing.</p>
<h2 local-id=3D"dd19f30bc9fd" id=3D"Task18-TechnicalDocument-2.2KeyPrincipl=
es=E2=80=93AWSWell-ArchitectedFramework"><strong>2.2 Key Principles =E2=80=
=93 AWS Well-Architected Framework</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"c763edc2-d4c6-4712-894a-bf3=
3caf8e874" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"07b7a362b52a"><strong>Pillar</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"7a8265ed3dde"><strong>Principle</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"2e8fe8d315f2"><strong>How We Achieved It</strong></p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b4673d3743af"><strong>Operational Excellence</strong></p></t=
d>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f55140d4ec4a"><strong>Structured, documented deployment proc=
ess</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d48d71fc8ad7"><strong>Step-by-step Nginx and ALB configurati=
on; Nginx logs and ALB health checks used for operational visibility</stron=
g></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"0fe4885a2e1d"><strong>Security</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"e44daf00f62d"><strong>HTTPS enforced across all sites</stron=
g></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"411993afba44"><strong>ACM SSL certificate on ALB listener (H=
TTPS:443); Certbot SSL on Nginx with HTTP-to-HTTPS redirect (302) enforced<=
/strong></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f90370380831"><strong>Reliability</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"edd8d78c19e6"><strong>Load balancer ensures high availabilit=
y for Site 3 and Site 4</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4233a003e5d9"><strong>ALB health checks on / endpoint detect=
 unhealthy instances; traffic automatically routed to healthy targets only<=
/strong></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"20ec8e32a222"><strong>Performance Efficiency</strong></p></t=
d>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"bfec6798d712"><strong>Traffic distributed across instances; =
optimised routing</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b23b42e76427"><strong>ALB round-robin distribution across tw=
o EC2 instances; Nginx serves static content directly without proxy overhea=
d</strong></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a7c95af04cab"><strong>Cost Optimisation</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"e6be13f4345e"><strong>Minimal EC2 instances; free-tier eligi=
ble services</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"480278e8e7e8"><strong>3 EC2 instances total (t2.micro); ACM =
certificates are free; ALB pay-per-LCU-hour</strong></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"62d1d9b07b96"><strong>Sustainability</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"288d77ef3af5"><strong>No over-provisioning; resources sized =
for workload</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"56f51ba791bb"><strong>t2.micro instances sufficient for demo=
/test workload; ALB scales to zero cost when idle</strong></p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h2 local-id=3D"1222d2f68192" id=3D"Task18-TechnicalDocument-2.3GoalsandObj=
ectives"><strong>2.3 Goals and Objectives</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"9effbf5d2707">Deploy Site 1 and Site 2 on a single Nginx EC2=
 instance using separate server blocks, each serving unique content (Hello =
from Site 1 / Hello from Site 2)</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"2eecf649d58e">Deploy Site 3 and Site 4 on two separate EC2 i=
nstances hosting the hello-world-flask application with per-instance modifi=
ed content</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"e5d3e81321e3">Create an Application Load Balancer with a tar=
get group containing both Flask EC2 instances, with health checks and round=
-robin distribution</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"55ec085b3ee5">Enable HTTPS for all four sites =E2=80=94 Cert=
bot/ACM on Nginx for Site 1 and 2; ACM SSL certificate on ALB for Site 3 an=
d 4</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"06cbe3c6d427">Configure Route 53 A records mapping site1=E2=
=80=93site4.karna.pushkar.cloud to the appropriate EC2 IP or ALB DNS name</=
p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"ac22266cccd7">Validate the complete setup: correct content p=
er domain, HTTPS padlock, and observable load balancing via page refresh</p=
></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"95c01d475c4d" id=3D"Task18-TechnicalDocument-2.4Constraints=
andAssumptions"><strong>2.4 Constraints and Assumptions</strong></h2>
<p local-id=3D"ab4b3cf3c40b"><strong>Constraints</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"ae4861f4b94b">Budget: Free-tier eligible t2.micro EC2 instan=
ces; ACM certificates are free; ALB has per-LCU-hour cost</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"4c1ac807335b">Time: Full implementation to be completed with=
in 3 hours</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"670f41f148a5">Technology: Stack is fixed =E2=80=94 Nginx, Py=
thon Flask, AWS EC2, ALB, ACM, Route 53, domain karna.pushkar.cloud</p></li=
>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"2c99a8d82288">Deployment: Manual deployment via SSH and AWS =
Console =E2=80=94 no CI/CD pipeline in this phase</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"5177a3196a77"><strong>Assumptions</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"375e210c7b8e">Domain karna.pushkar.cloud is registered and i=
ts Route 53 hosted zone is active</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"48dd1b05f3ad">EC2 instances are launched with Ubuntu 22.04 L=
TS on t2.micro</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"ede35c620809">Security Groups allow inbound SSH (22), HTTP (=
80), and HTTPS (443) from 0.0.0.0/0</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"cfb57331543e">Flask application (hello-world-flask) runs on =
port 5000 on Site 3 and Site 4 EC2 instances</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"bad7a7870577">ACM certificate is requested for site3.karna.p=
ushkar.cloud and site4.karna.pushkar.cloud and validated via Route 53 DNS v=
alidation</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h1 local-id=3D"00bd1f7a9029" id=3D"Task18-TechnicalDocument-3.Architecture=
andInfrastructure"><strong>3. Architecture and Infrastructure</strong></h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"576e32fc4684" id=3D"Task18-TechnicalDocument-3.1Infrastruct=
ureOverview"><strong>3.1 Infrastructure Overview</strong></h2><span class=
=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedd=
ed-manual-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image image-center" alt=
=3D"image (9)-20260322-115812.png" width=3D"468" loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"7e=
c6dcc068ab6688f1eb3006061f65ba964dda5967bd0128fb6e84eff9f48660" data-image-=
src=3D"https://iamops.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1864990774/im=
age%20(9)-20260322-115812.png?version=3D2&amp;modificationDate=3D1774180741=
706&amp;cacheVersion=3D1&amp;api=3Dv2" data-height=3D"1011" data-width=3D"1=
898" data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1885635=
350" data-linked-resource-version=3D"2" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attach=
ment" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image (9)-20260322-115812.png" =
data-base-url=3D"https://iamops.atlassian.net/wiki" data-linked-resource-co=
ntent-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1864990774" d=
ata-linked-resource-container-version=3D"2" data-media-id=3D"7e512ff7-a1aa-=
4e93-9a50-047b9a044ffd" data-media-type=3D"file" height=3D"249"></span>
<p local-id=3D"b6f85ccf0aab"></p>
<p local-id=3D"d06fd54baed8">The solution uses three EC2 instances across t=
wo hosting tiers and one ALB:</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"62161447-478d-43ff-a5d9-080=
919300d05" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"627b32782f36"><strong>Component</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"23b8790dd8e4"><strong>Resource</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"b743ad7c2380"><strong>Detail</strong></p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b7c39e0fe3a9"><strong>Nginx EC2 (EC2-1)</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"042fbb36b289"><strong>t2.micro =E2=80=93 Ubuntu 22.04</stron=
g></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"79726687c0f4"><strong>Hosts Site 1 and Site 2 via Nginx serv=
er blocks on port 80/443</strong></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"382a00cea31d"><strong>Flask EC2 (EC2-2)</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"32697c30c674"><strong>t2.micro =E2=80=93 Ubuntu 22.04</stron=
g></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"feede617cc6f"><strong>Hosts Site 3 =E2=80=93 hello-world-fla=
sk modified to show "Hello from Site 3" on port 5000</strong></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"dde194589221"><strong>Flask EC2 (EC2-3)</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b569c018ace1"><strong>t2.micro =E2=80=93 Ubuntu 22.04</stron=
g></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"11d8d7466b11"><strong>Hosts Site 4 =E2=80=93 hello-world-fla=
sk modified to show "Hello from Site 4" on port 5000</strong></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"8fe286175134"><strong>Application Load Balancer</strong></p>=
</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d14d15ff0877"><strong>ALB =E2=80=93 Internet-facing</strong>=
</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ee5372752795"><strong>HTTP:80 and HTTPS:443 listeners; forwa=
rds to Flask target group</strong></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"51a901ba9b2f"><strong>Target Group</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"e26012f195b5"><strong>flask-target-group</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"1ec4747f8e0b"><strong>EC2-2 and EC2-3 registered on port 500=
0; health check path: /</strong></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"6f7e4fcc5839"><strong>ACM Certificate</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a94a32c7dcac"><strong>*.karna.pushkar.cloud</strong></p></td=
>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"512704977ccb"><strong>Covers site3 and site4 subdomains; att=
ached to ALB HTTPS listener</strong></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b96e8c76c0b2"><strong>Route 53</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"734e1cf35075"><strong>karna.pushkar.cloud hosted zone</stron=
g></p></td>
