=80=E2=94=80=E2=94=98</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"b76e72586cf1">For Nginx-hosted sites: The user's DNS query r=
esolves to the EC2-1 public IP via Route 53. Nginx receives the request on =
port 443, matches the server_name directive to the correct server block, an=
d serves the corresponding /var/www/siteN/index.html content. HTTP requests=
 on port 80 are redirected to HTTPS by Certbot's redirect configuration.</p=
>
<p local-id=3D"2b1c64a72897">For ALB-hosted sites: The user's DNS query res=
olves to the ALB DNS name via Route 53. The ALB HTTPS listener (port 443) r=
eceives the request, terminates TLS using the ACM certificate, and forwards=
 the request to one of the two healthy Flask EC2 instances in the target gr=
oup via round-robin load balancing. Refreshing the page alternates the resp=
onse between "Hello from Site 3" and "Hello from Site 4".</p>
