<h1 local-id=3D"7d0b8eee7ecc" id=3D"Task18-TechnicalDocument-4.DevelopmentP=
ractices"><strong>4. Development Practices</strong></h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"282e88c8423f" id=3D"Task18-TechnicalDocument-4.1VersionCont=
rol"><strong>4.1 Version Control</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"e12e1bbd9d1f">Base application sourced from the public GitHu=
b repository pushkar-iamops/hello-world-flask using git clone</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"b89dfc2b88a4">Each EC2 instance (EC2-2 for Site 3, EC2-3 for=
 Site 4) clones the same repository and modifies the Flask app's return mes=
sage to display a unique per-site identifier (Hello from Site 3 / Hello fro=
m Site 4)</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"89970847a78f">Nginx configuration files (/etc/nginx/sites-av=
ailable/site1 and site2) are treated as infrastructure configuration files =
=E2=80=94 stored in version control for reproducibility</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"96414de77b2d" id=3D"Task18-TechnicalDocument-4.2ContinuousI=
ntegration"><strong>4.2 Continuous Integration</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"f410321f2bf9">Deployment is manual in this phase: SSH into e=
ach EC2 instance, git clone the repository, modify the application, and sta=
rt the Flask server</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"ed15eeb9c5b3">Nginx configuration changes are validated usin=
g sudo nginx -t before reloading the service =E2=80=94 preventing syntax er=
rors from causing service disruptions</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"05fdc4e5c771">Future enhancement: GitHub Actions to auto-dep=
loy Flask application updates to EC2 instances on push to main, and to auto=
-reload Nginx configuration after changes</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"be59cbedf4a8" id=3D"Task18-TechnicalDocument-4.3AutomatedTe=
sting"><strong>4.3 Automated Testing</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"895a5709a0ff">Site 1 and Site 2 are validated by loading <a =
class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://site1.karna.pushkar.cloud" rel=3D"n=
ofollow">https://site1.karna.pushkar.cloud</a> and <a class=3D"external-lin=
k" href=3D"https://site2.karna.pushkar.cloud" rel=3D"nofollow">https://site=
2.karna.pushkar.cloud</a> in a browser and confirming the correct content a=
nd HTTPS padlock</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"2f75ef8d6871">Site 3 and Site 4 load balancing is validated =
by repeatedly refreshing the ALB DNS endpoint and observing the response al=
ternating between "Hello from Site 3" and "Hello from Site 4"</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"fab380a49965">ALB health checks on the / endpoint continuous=
ly monitor EC2-2 and EC2-3 =E2=80=94 only healthy instances receive traffic=
</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"b4746608f9c7">SSL validation is confirmed by the browser HTT=
PS padlock and the absence of certificate warnings on all four sites</p></l=
i>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"9bea5dcb1255" id=3D"Task18-TechnicalDocument-4.4CodeQuality=
andAnalysis"><strong>4.4 Code Quality and Analysis</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"3e1473b06bd1">Nginx configuration is validated using sudo ng=
inx -t before every reload =E2=80=94 this catches directive syntax errors, =
mismatched brackets, and conflicting server_name definitions</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"c02c7d2330c9">Flask application modifications are minimal (s=
ingle message string change) =E2=80=94 reducing the risk of introducing bug=
s into the base application</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"6973a6a4eaab">Nginx server blocks are organized in separate =
files under /etc/nginx/sites-available/ and symlinked to /etc/nginx/sites-e=
nabled/ =E2=80=94 maintaining clean separation between site configurations<=
/p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"c136bfac3453">Only one server block uses listen 80 default_s=
erver =E2=80=94 avoiding Nginx conflicts when multiple server blocks listen=
 on the same port</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h1 local-id=3D"dcfc988464a9" id=3D"Task18-TechnicalDocument-5.Deploymentan=
dReleaseManagement"><strong>5. Deployment and Release Management</strong></=
h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"be237cda44ad" id=3D"Task18-TechnicalDocument-5.1DeploymentS=
trategy"><strong>5.1 Deployment Strategy</strong></h2>
<p local-id=3D"9159b07fbcd8">The deployment is organized into four sequenti=
al phases, each building on the previous:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"929b2ead79c3">Phase 1 =E2=80=93 Nginx Direct Hosting (Site 1=
 &amp; 2): EC2-1 provisioned, Nginx installed, website directories and inde=
x files created, server blocks configured, sites enabled and validated on H=
TTP</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"8c1446edd500">Phase 2 =E2=80=93 Flask Backend Deployment (Si=
te 3 &amp; 4): EC2-2 and EC2-3 provisioned, Flask application cloned from G=
itHub, per-instance message modified, Flask server started on port 5000</p>=
</li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"d9e12fccd422">Phase 3 =E2=80=93 ALB Setup: Target group crea=
ted with EC2-2 and EC2-3 registered, health checks configured, ALB created =
with HTTP:80 listener forwarding to the target group, load balancing valida=
ted via ALB DNS</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"1bae279d8ec4">Phase 4 =E2=80=93 SSL + DNS: Certbot SSL confi=
gured on Nginx EC2 for site1 and site2 with HTTP-to-HTTPS redirect; ACM cer=
tificate requested and DNS-validated for ALB; HTTPS listener (443) added to=
 ALB with ACM certificate; Route 53 A records created for all four sites</p=
></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"d724d7a2bca0" id=3D"Task18-TechnicalDocument-5.2Configurati=
onManagement"><strong>5.2 Configuration Management</strong></h2>
<p local-id=3D"fe59c3d7a184"><strong>Nginx Server Block =E2=80=94 Site 1 (/=
etc/nginx/sites-available/site1):</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"0b50af12fcc0"><strong>nginx</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">server =
{
    listen 80 default_server;
    server_name site1.karna.pushkar.cloud;

    root /var/www/site1;
    index index.html;

    location / {
        try_files $uri $uri/ =3D404;
    }
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"363255ef4e5c"><strong>Nginx Server Block =E2=80=94 Site 2 (/=
etc/nginx/sites-available/site2):</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"245219e31172"><strong>nginx</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">server =
{
    listen 80;
    server_name site2.karna.pushkar.cloud;

    root /var/www/site2;
    index index.html;

    location / {
        try_files $uri $uri/ =3D404;
    }
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
