<h1 local-id=3D"4e449fc1f36a" id=3D"Task18-TechnicalDocument-6.Monitoringan=
dIncidentManagement"><strong>6. Monitoring and Incident Management</strong>=
</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"870777a77be1" id=3D"Task18-TechnicalDocument-6.1MonitoringT=
oolsandMetrics"><strong>6.1 Monitoring Tools and Metrics</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"20207114dffa">ALB Health Checks: Continuous HTTP health chec=
ks on / for EC2-2 and EC2-3 =E2=80=94 instances failing health checks are r=
emoved from the target group and no longer receive traffic</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"ac5d92b70059">Nginx Access and Error Logs: /var/log/nginx/ac=
cess.log and /var/log/nginx/error.log capture all requests and server-side =
errors for Site 1 and Site 2</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"dc5983d4ea3d">EC2 Instance Status Checks: AWS Console EC2 in=
stance status checks (System reachability and Instance reachability) monito=
r the health of all three EC2 instances</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"898d9578333f">CloudWatch (Future): ALB publishes RequestCoun=
t, TargetResponseTime, and HTTPCode_Target_5XX_Count metrics to CloudWatch =
=E2=80=94 available for dashboard and alarm configuration</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"cf797b029c7d">Browser Validation: Manual validation by loadi=
ng all four site URLs in a browser confirms correct content, HTTPS, and loa=
d balancing behavior</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"a12a1c33861e" id=3D"Task18-TechnicalDocument-6.2Alertingand=
Notification"><strong>6.2 Alerting and Notification</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"579690246144">ALB Unhealthy Target: CloudWatch alarm on Heal=
thyHostCount &lt; 1 =E2=86=92 SNS notification to the operations team if al=
l Flask instances become unhealthy</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"8ba451a22e8b">EC2 Status Check Failure: CloudWatch alarm on =
StatusCheckFailed_Instance =E2=86=92 alert if any EC2 host becomes unreacha=
ble</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"31bb9d33d1c8">Nginx Service Failure: systemd OnFailure=3D di=
rective on the Nginx service can trigger an alert or restart on crash</p></=
li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"761041216992">SSL Expiry (Certbot): Certbot auto-renewal cro=
n job runs twice daily =E2=80=94 Let's Encrypt certificates auto-renew befo=
re expiry; ACM certificates managed by AWS renew automatically with no manu=
al intervention</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"dd7e9196f5ac" id=3D"Task18-TechnicalDocument-6.3IncidentMan=
agement"><strong>6.3 Incident Management</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"ac96faa3-838c-4454-aa5c-956=
5c0a242ca" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"87e96550248b"><strong>Severity</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"3bda90fe1c07"><strong>Example</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"5971abb0f386"><strong>Response</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"071520c84814"><strong>Resolution Target</strong></p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"6e0257033db0"><strong>P1 =E2=80=93 Critical</strong></p></td=
>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c96052a4fa16"><strong>All four sites down</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ffeababd129a"><strong>Check EC2 status; restart Nginx; check=
 ALB health; verify Security Group rules</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"1e30526b8e15"><strong>&lt; 15 minutes</strong></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a20d24ba7e37"><strong>P2 =E2=80=93 High</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"246939778c19"><strong>Site 1 or Site 2 returning 404 or 502<=
/strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"09fa5b264dae"><strong>Check Nginx error log; verify server_n=
ame in server block; confirm site root path and index.html exist</strong></=
p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3316afe82f1f"><strong>&lt; 30 minutes</strong></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f58dc4114a74"><strong>P3 =E2=80=93 Medium</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"0999f63f0f26"><strong>ALB shows one unhealthy target</strong=
></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"79fee9ffcfd4"><strong>SSH into unhealthy EC2; check Flask pr=
ocess is running on port 5000; restart if needed</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"859420c7ccf8"><strong>&lt; 1 hour</strong></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"eec4fabee7a2"><strong>P4 =E2=80=93 Low</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"7645295fb0ec"><strong>SSL certificate warning on one site</s=
trong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a783b8dcf84f"><strong>Run sudo certbot renew --dry-run to ch=
eck renewal; verify ACM cert status in console</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"6a904d97c028"><strong>&lt; 2 hours</strong></p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<h1 local-id=3D"f783392a6ba4" id=3D"Task18-TechnicalDocument-7.Security&amp=
;Compliance"><strong>7. Security &amp; Compliance</strong></h1>
<p local-id=3D"7466f7d800b3"><strong>Infrastructure Security:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"d2598e0b444e">HTTPS Enforced: All four sites enforce HTTPS =
=E2=80=94 Certbot configures HTTP-to-HTTPS redirect (301) on Nginx for Site=
 1 and 2; ALB HTTP listener can be configured to redirect to HTTPS for Site=
 3 and 4</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"b85f6ca3eab5">ACM Certificate: AWS Certificate Manager provi=
des a managed, auto-renewing SSL certificate attached to the ALB HTTPS list=
ener (port 443) =E2=80=94 covering site3 and site4 subdomains</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"43e0f808387a">Let's Encrypt via Certbot: Free, auto-renewing=
 SSL certificates installed on the Nginx EC2 for site1 and site2 =E2=80=94 =
renewed automatically via Certbot's cron job</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"6366f9eb8b5f">Security Group Rules: EC2 instances only allow=
 inbound traffic on required ports (22 for SSH, 80 for HTTP, 443 for HTTPS,=
 5000 for Flask from ALB only) =E2=80=94 all other inbound ports are denied=
</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"fa38ecbe8aeb">TLS Communication: All traffic between users a=
nd the application is encrypted via TLS 1.2/1.3 =E2=80=94 no plaintext HTTP=
 in production paths</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"bea7b3f269e9"><strong>Identity and Access Management (IAM):<=
/strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"6944e7d25137">EC2 IAM Role: EC2 instances are assigned minim=
al IAM roles =E2=80=94 no broad permissions; ACM certificate management is =
performed from a secured admin workstation via the AWS Console</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"dff5dfabe2b8">Least Privilege: IAM permissions for Route 53 =
record creation and ACM certificate validation are scoped to the specific h=
osted zone ARN =E2=80=94 not account-wide</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"d0eb069ea08c">SSH Access: EC2 SSH access (port 22) is restri=
cted to the administrator's IP in production Security Group configurations;=
 during lab/demo, open to 0.0.0.0/0 for convenience only</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"d61e57b70416">ACM DNS Validation: Certificate domain ownersh=
ip is validated via Route 53 DNS CNAME records =E2=80=94 no email validatio=
n; automated and auditable</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h1 local-id=3D"e11d6f00739a" id=3D"Task18-TechnicalDocument-8.CostOptimisa=
tion"><strong>8. Cost Optimisation</strong></h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"862ad9da9f18" id=3D"Task18-TechnicalDocument-TotalCostofOwn=
