<p local-id=3D"6a1e6e1e9bee"><strong>Cost Optimisation Recommendations:</st=
rong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"f68caee8aa9d">Reserved Instances: Converting all three EC2 i=
nstances to 1-year Reserved Instances reduces compute cost by ~40% =E2=80=
=94 saving approximately $10/month across all three instances</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"ec53c8d4064d">Auto Scaling Group for Flask Instances: Replac=
ing the two fixed Flask EC2 instances with an Auto Scaling Group allows sca=
le-to-zero during off-peak hours =E2=80=94 potentially eliminating EC2 cost=
s for Site 3 and Site 4 when not in use</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"b7c9c279a863">Single Nginx EC2 for Multiple Sites: Hosting S=
ite 1 and Site 2 on a single EC2 instance via Nginx virtual hosts (rather t=
han two separate instances) saves $8.47/month compared to a one-instance-pe=
r-site approach</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"d0ce3e24deee">ACM vs Third-Party SSL: Using ACM for ALB and =
Certbot (Let's Encrypt) for Nginx eliminates SSL certificate purchase costs=
 entirely =E2=80=94 saving $50=E2=80=93$200/year per domain compared to com=
mercial certificates</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"3d0f3d418afc"><strong>Business Value Analysis:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"6f61cf8ae5c5">Deployment Speed: Manual deployment of all fou=
r sites completed within 3 hours =E2=80=94 demonstrates the speed of AWS-na=
tive tooling for rapid prototyping and demo environment setup</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"7abd187a43ab">Load Balancing ROI: ALB-based distribution for=
 Site 3 and Site 4 means either Flask EC2 can be stopped for maintenance wi=
thout any downtime =E2=80=94 eliminating single-point-of-failure risk at a =
cost of ~$16/month for the ALB</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"0e29e1a6b658">SSL at Zero Cost: ACM and Certbot eliminate SS=
L certificate costs entirely while providing the same security posture as c=
ommercial certificates</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"2f1f35342119">Scalability: The ALB + target group architectu=
re allows adding additional Flask instances to the target group with zero d=
owntime =E2=80=94 supporting future traffic growth without architectural ch=
anges</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
