<h1 local-id=3D"7595aa9c69e4" id=3D"Task18-TechnicalDocument-11.ContinuousI=
mprovement">11. Continuous Improvement</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"6e22f1ebaf09" id=3D"Task18-TechnicalDocument-11.1Feedbackan=
dRetrospectives">11.1 Feedback and Retrospectives</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"a2a4ce24656e">Post-implementation review confirmed that Ngin=
x's default_server directive on Site 1 is required to prevent Nginx from re=
turning a 404 for requests that don't match any server_name =E2=80=94 this =
is now documented as a mandatory configuration step for all multi-site Ngin=
x deployments</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"b67bc96894be">The team noted that starting Flask with python=
3 hello.py directly in an SSH session means the process dies when the sessi=
on closes =E2=80=94 a future iteration will configure Flask as a systemd se=
rvice or use gunicorn with a process manager to ensure persistence</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"3e3f31b3723d">DNS propagation for Route 53 A records was obs=
erved to complete within 60 seconds for Alias records pointing to the ALB =
=E2=80=94 faster than expected, reducing the validation wait time</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"3161ff4833c9">ACM certificate DNS validation via Route 53 co=
mpleted in under 2 minutes =E2=80=94 significantly faster than email valida=
tion and now the team's preferred validation method for all future certific=
ate requests</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"2f01d68b5192" id=3D"Task18-TechnicalDocument-11.2IterativeE=
nhancements">11.2 Iterative Enhancements</h2>
<p local-id=3D"0fe49741df3f">The following improvements are planned for sub=
sequent iterations:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"e0a95fbfc89d"><strong>Infrastructure as Code:</strong> Migra=
te all EC2, ALB, target group, Security Group, and Route 53 record provisio=
ning to Terraform =E2=80=94 enabling one-command reproducible deployment of=
 the entire multi-site architecture</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"431d225f80f9"><strong>CI/CD Pipeline:</strong> GitHub Action=
s workflow to automatically deploy Flask application updates to EC2-2 and E=
C2-3 on push to main, and to reload Nginx configuration after site1/site2 c=
ontent changes</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"6943dbbd8730"><strong>Auto Scaling Group:</strong> Replace t=
he two fixed Flask EC2 instances with an ASG behind the ALB =E2=80=94 enabl=
ing automatic scale-out during traffic spikes and scale-in during quiet per=
iods to reduce costs</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"d06ace01376d"><strong>Nginx as Reverse Proxy for Flask:</str=
ong> Route Site 3 and Site 4 traffic through Nginx on port 80/443 as a reve=
rse proxy to Flask on port 5000 =E2=80=94 eliminating the need to expose po=
rt 5000 directly and improving security</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"e10c2f6034db"><strong>Centralised Logging:</strong> Ship Ngi=
nx access logs and Flask application logs to CloudWatch Logs for centralise=
d, searchable, and alertable log management</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"91a4322c6963"><strong>CloudWatch Dashboard:</strong> Build a=
 CloudWatch Dashboard showing ALB RequestCount, TargetResponseTime, and Ngi=
nx EC2 CPU utilisation in real time</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h1 local-id=3D"82d7d048d8cd" id=3D"Task18-TechnicalDocument-12.Conclusion"=
>12. Conclusion</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"fab8be03a52e" id=3D"Task18-TechnicalDocument-12.1Summary">1=
2.1 Summary</h2>
<p local-id=3D"6acee3ced9b2">This document has described the complete imple=
mentation of a multi-website hosting architecture on AWS for ABC Technologi=
es, combining direct Nginx hosting with ALB-based load balancing. The key o=
utcomes achieved are:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"2415d8b5e4ca"><strong>Four Sites Deployed:</strong> Site 1 a=
nd Site 2 hosted on a single EC2 instance via Nginx virtual hosts; Site 3 a=
nd Site 4 hosted on separate EC2 instances via the Flask application, distr=
ibuted by an ALB</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"8d7ed3fe7431"><strong>HTTPS Enforced:</strong> All four site=
s secured with SSL =E2=80=94 Certbot/Let's Encrypt on Nginx with HTTP-to-HT=
TPS redirect; ACM certificate on ALB HTTPS listener</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"ab8f1b39344d"><strong>Load Balancing Validated:</strong> ALB=
 round-robin distribution confirmed by observing alternating "Hello from Si=
te 3" and "Hello from Site 4" responses on page refresh</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"11415bc8e7fe"><strong>DNS Routing Configured:</strong> Route=
 53 A records and Alias records correctly route each subdomain to the appro=
priate infrastructure endpoint</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"fcab7a962376"><strong>Completed Within 3 Hours:</strong> Ful=
l provisioning, configuration, SSL, DNS, and validation completed within th=
e target time constraint</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"692369c6d723" id=3D"Task18-TechnicalDocument-12.2NextSteps"=
>12.2 Next Steps</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"254b69deed7e">Automate the full deployment using Terraform f=
or infrastructure and GitHub Actions for application deployment</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"b1d1ed9cc736">Replace direct Flask startup with systemd serv=
ice or Gunicorn process manager for production-grade process management</p>=
</li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"fcc973df363d">Add Auto Scaling Group behind the ALB for Site=
 3 and Site 4 to handle variable traffic</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"79c947db0699">Implement CloudWatch alarms for ALB unhealthy =
host count and EC2 CPU utilisation</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"2ee2bdcc0f2a">Evaluate migrating to AWS ECS (Fargate) for co=
ntainerised Flask hosting to eliminate EC2 management overhead entirely</p>=
</li>
</ul>
<hr>
